{"lemma":"غُبْرِ","slug":"غُبْرِ","root":"غ.ب.ر","root_slug":"غ-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31334","n31339","n31340","n31341","n31343","n31354"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become dust-colored"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/iɣ.bar.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31334","headword_ar":"غَبَرَ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gubuwrN","text_ar":"غُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remained, lasted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continued:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA:) and (Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, JK)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tarried, stayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waited."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, Zbd, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, passed, passed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) It is sometimes used in this latter sense; (Msb;) and thus it has two contr. significations. (Msb, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was future."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.)       -A2-  See also 9.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabira","text_ar":"غَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 5, last two sentences. ―         -b2-  Also, this last, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabarN","text_ar":"غَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) said of a wound, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a corrupt state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became in a healing state, and then became recrudescent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was always recrudescent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became in a healing state upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over, corruptness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it healed externally while in a withering state internally."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-  And [hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabira","text_ar":"غَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bore rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hid enmity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violent hatred, in his heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","IKtt"]},{"entry_id":"n31339","headword_ar":"غُبْرٌ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A remain, remainder, remnant, relic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"residue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) of a thing; (K;) generally, of the blood of the menses, (K,) and of milk in the udder: (S, K:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~arN","text_ar":"غُبَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~arN","text_ar":"غُبَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guborN","text_ar":"غُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [but if so it is extr.:] (TA:) or the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guborN","text_ar":"غُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agobaArN","text_ar":"اَغْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~arN","text_ar":"غُبَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAbirN","text_ar":"غَابِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant]; (A'Obeyd, TA;) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (A'Obeyd, S, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~araAtN","text_ar":"غُبَّرَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. pl.; i. e., pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~arN","text_ar":"غُبَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A'Obeyd, TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA guborN mino labanK","text_ar":"بِهَا غُبْرٌ مِنْ لَبَنٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In her"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a remain of milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~aru","text_ar":"غُبَّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayoDi","text_ar":"الحَيْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remains"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the blood]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the menses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guboruhu","text_ar":"غُبْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 37.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaraDi","text_ar":"المَرَضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~aru","text_ar":"غُبَّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remains of the disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayoli","text_ar":"اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~aru","text_ar":"غُبَّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The last part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the remains, of the night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a trad. of 'Amr Ibn-El-Ás,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA taA^ab~aTatoniY AlA_imaA='u walaA","text_ar":"مَا تَاَبَّطَتْنِى الاـِمَا=ءُ وَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA=liY","text_ar":"المَا=لِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamalatoniY AlbagaAyaA fiY gub~araAti","text_ar":"حَمَلَتْنِى البَغَايَا فِى غُبَّرَاتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Female slaves did not carry me under their armpits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e., female slaves did not have the office of rearing me,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor did prostitutes carry me in the remains of the rags used for the menses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^aholi AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"مِنْ اَهْلِ الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falamo yaboqa A_il~aA gub~araAtN","text_ar":"فَلَمْ يَبْقَ اـِلَّا غُبَّرَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholi","text_ar":"اَهْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~aru","text_ar":"غُبَّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different relations, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And there remained not save remains of the people of the Scripture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the remains"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.) And in a trad. of Mo'áwiyeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bifanaAy^ihi A^aEonuzN dar~uhun~a guyorN","text_ar":"بِفَنَايِهِ اَعْنُزٌ دَرُّهُنَّ غُيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the court of his house were some she-goats whose flow of milk was a"},{"kind":"text","text":"mere"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remain"},{"kind":"text","text":"of what it had been,] meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAbirN","text_ar":"غَابِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31340","headword_ar":"غِبْرٌ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concealed enmity and violent hatred:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gimorN","text_ar":"غِمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31341","headword_ar":"غَبَرٌ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A remaining, lasting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magobarN","text_ar":"مَغْبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 225.) ―         -b2-  [And by some of the grammarians it is used as signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"future:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAbirN","text_ar":"غَابِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in the interior of the foot of a camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A morbid affection"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a vein,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that will hardly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in nowise, be cured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gabirN","text_ar":"غَبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhiyapu Algabari","text_ar":"دَاهِيَةُ الغَبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(said by A'Obeyd to be from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juroHN gabirN","text_ar":"جُرْحٌ غَبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], TA) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of great magnitude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like whereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is such that no way of escape therefrom will be found:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, * K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affliction, that will hardly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in nowise, depart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person who opposes thee, disagreeing with thee, and then returns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has regard, to thy saying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) whence the saying, mentioned by AZ,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA liTalabi AlmiraA='i","text_ar":"اـِلَّا لِطَلَبِ المِرَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA gab~arato","text_ar":"مَا غَبَّرَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See 2, last sentence.]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~aA='u Algabari","text_ar":"صَمَّا=ءُ الغَبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a verse of El- Hirmázee in praise of El-Mundhir Ibn-Járood, to whom it is applied, is expl. by Z as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The serpent that dwells near to a small water in a place where it collects and stagnates, and that will not be approached."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algabaru","text_ar":"الغَبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water little in quantity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gubaArN","text_ar":"غُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31343","headword_ar":"غُبَرٌ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fish;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gawobarN","text_ar":"غَوْبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31354","headword_ar":"غُبَّرٌ","root":"gbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gub~araAtN","text_ar":"غُبَّرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guborN","text_ar":"غُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", passim."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}